stylometry: The data mining method that we used is the cluster method. The cluster method consisted of us finding a large set of data, making the calculations and running solver to find the optimal solutions. First, after finding the data, we found the standardized data by taking the average divided by the standard deviation of the data. After that, we used the sumxmy2 function and the min function to find the minimum of the data. We then used the index function to place the data into their appropriate subsets. Lastly, we used the match function to match the subsets and indexes. We performed solver to find the optimal subsets for the data.
